value.title: Trump, Pence meet for 1st time since Capitol riot
value.excerpt: President Trump lashed out at Mike Pence last week after the vice president said he lacked authority under the Constitution to overturn election results on the president’s behalf.

value.title: Manchin calls second Trump impeachment bid 'ill-advised': 'Let the judicial system do its job'
value.excerpt: House Democrats' attempt to impeach President Trump for a second time in connection with last week's riot at the U.S. Capitol is "so ill-advised," Sen. Joe Manchin, D-W.Va. told "Special Report" Monday.

value.title: Critics mock NY Gov. Cuomo's sudden denunciation of lockdowns, suggest Trump hacked his Twitter account
value.excerpt: Democratic New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo raised eyebrows on Monday for his drastic shift on lockdowns during the pandemic.

value.title: Gidley blasts Democrats' 'disgusting tactic' of claiming anyone pro-Trump 'agrees with lawless thugs'
value.excerpt: Former Deputy White House Press Secretary Hogan Gidley ripped into Democrats and their supporters in Hollywood and the media Monday for making blanket claims that anyone who supports President Trump is also supportive of the "lawless thugs" who attacked the U.S. Capitol last week.

value.title: Pamela Anderson appeals Trump to pardon Assange and stand up for free speech
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: Supporters of WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange are making a final appeal to the outgoing President Trump to show his commitment to free speech by granting a full pardon to the jailed publisher.

value.title: Angela Merkel rips Twitter's 'problematic' Trump ban
value.excerpt: German Chancellor Angela Merkel considers President Donald Trump's eviction from Twitter by the company "problematic," her spokesman said Monday.

value.title: Cuomo, De Blasio are 'banking on a bailout from Biden' while lockdowns are in effect: Gasparino
value.excerpt: New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo and New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio are prolonging the shutdown of New York because they are expecting a bailout from the incoming Biden administration and the Democrat-controlled Congress.

value.title: Washington monument closes through Biden's inauguration due to 'credible threats'
value.excerpt: The National Park Service said Monday it is suspending tours of the Washington Monument until Jan. 24 or longer due to "credible threats" from groups involved in the violence at the U.S. Capitol on Jan. 6.

value.title: Turley: Democrats 'impulse buy' impeachment of Trump would have 'very serious implications'
value.excerpt: George Washington University law professor Jonathan Turley said he doesn’t think Democrats should go forward with a "snap impeachment," explaining that the process is supposed be "deliberative," not impulsive.

value.title: Melania Trump ‘disappointed and disheartened’ over Capitol attack: ‘Nation must heal in a civil manner'
value.excerpt: The deadly riots unfolded on Wednesday after a rally to support President Trump descended into a mob that stormed the Capitol during the certification of the Electoral College vote.

value.title: Biden announces William Burns for CIA director
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden announced Ambassador William Burns as his nominee for director of the CIA on Monday.

value.title: Right back to where we were last year: Dems seek Trump impeachment
Pelosi says lawmakers moving forward with impeachment, calls Trump 'imminent threat' to 'our Democracy'
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Sunday said the House will be moving forward with a resolution to impeach Donald Trump, whom she referred to in a letter to her colleagues as an “imminent threat” to both the U.S. Constitution and Democracy.

value.title: DC Delegate Norton to introduce resolution to censure  Trump as ‘only remedy that can pass both chambers’
value.excerpt: House of Representatives Delegate Eleanor Holmes Norton on Sunday called on Congress to censure President Donald Trump for his alleged incitement of Wednesday’s riot at the U.S. Capitol.

value.title: Secret Service investigating death threats against Pence
value.excerpt: The U.S. Secret Service is investigating death threats against Vice President Mike Pence made by pro-Trump lawyer Lin Wood, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Trump to highlight border wall topping 400 miles with Texas visit during last full week in office
value.excerpt: With just over a week remaining in his term, President Trump is expected to celebrate progress on one of his featured campaign promises: a wall along the U.S.-Mexico border.

value.title: Dershowitz calls Trump impeachment a 'loaded weapon' that would be 'so dangerous to the Constitution'
value.excerpt: Harvard Law professor emeritus and constitutional law scholar Alan Dershowitz said that while he does not believe it would result in a Senate trial, impeaching President Trump over what he said in an address prior to protesters storming the Capitol building on Wednesday would provide a "loaded weapon"

value.title: Google, Microsoft, Verizon on Biden Inauguration Committee donor list
value.excerpt: Google, Microsoft, and Verizon are among President-elect Joe Biden's Inauguration Committee donors.

value.title: Roy Blunt balks at attempt to impeach Trump again: ‘Not going to happen’
value.excerpt: Roy Blunt, R-Mo., Friday balked at the idea of a second impeachment of President Trump.

value.title: Nancy Pelosi, in ‘60 Minutes’ interview, slams Trump as ‘deranged,’ calls for ‘prosecution’
value.excerpt: President Trump is "deranged, unhinged, dangerous," and deserving of prosecution, House Speaker Nancy Pelosi says in an interview scheduled to air Sunday night on "60 Minutes."

value.title: Biden: Trump 'not above the law. Justice serves the people — it doesn’t protect the powerful'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden said on Twitter Saturday that President Trump is “not above the law,” after the House announced it would be bringing forth articles of impeachment on Monday.

value.title: GOP Sen. Toomey: Trump 'committed impeachable offenses'
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Pat Toomey, Pa., said that President Trump “committed impeachable offenses” in his efforts to throw out the results of the 2020 presidential election.

value.title: Trump Twitter ban will be ‘exploited’ by ‘enemies' of free speech 'around the world,’ Russian dissident Navaln
value.excerpt: Russian opposition leader Alexey Navalny called Twitter’s ban of President Trump an “unacceptable act of censorship” that could be exploited by oppressive governments around the world.

value.title: Brit Hume: Twitter's reasons for banning Trump are 'pure editorial judgments'
value.excerpt: Fox News Senior Political Analyst Brit Hume is calling out big social media companies for making the decision to ban President Trump's accounts based on what he says are "pure editorial judgments."

value.title: Nikki Haley says Trump Twitter ban is 'what happens in China'
value.excerpt: Former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley on Friday reacted to the permanent suspension of President Trump’s Twitter account, describing it as an instance of "silencing" of the kind that happens in communist China.

value.title: Trump's standing in GOP takes a hit after Capitol riots, Georgia loss: 'This hurts,' strategist says
value.excerpt: Trump's clout with fellow Republicans takes a hit after the roughest week of his presidency.

value.title: LIVE UPDATES: Trump permanently banned from Twitter
value.excerpt: Follow for the latest updates on the fallout from the riot at the U.S. Capitol.

value.title: Biden says Cruz, Hawley part of ‘big lie’ -- while senators claim they are being called Nazis
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden said Friday that Sens. Ted Cruz, R-Texas, and Josh Hawley, R-Mo., should be "flat beaten" in their next elections for their part in spreading "the big lie," a term the senators said was an effort to cast them as Nazis.

value.title: Kamala Harris’ top economic advisor is another BlackRock exec
value.excerpt: BlackRock is cementing its position as the Biden administration’s go-to Wall Street firm. Vice-President-elect Kamala Harris on Friday said she’s selected BlackRock’s Global Chief Investment

value.title: Ilhan Omar says Trump 'will be impeached'
value.excerpt: Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., vowed on Friday that President Trump would be impeached after this week's riots, which have prompted widespread criticism of the president and his rhetoric following November's election.
